    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Create and confirm a recognition test (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>For Japan, impairment is conducted in two main steps.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create and confirm a recognition test (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For Japan, impairment is conducted in two main steps.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The first step is to test whether an impairment is needed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The second step is to calculate the impairment amount if needed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use this task to learn how to run the two step process in a recognition test and get it ready for posting.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In order to complete this procedure, the Fixed Asset configuration key must be selected.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure was created using the demo data company JPMF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Periodic tasks &gt; Impairment recognition (Method I: on a bigger group than CGU).</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For method 2, go to Fixed assets &gt; Periodic tasks &gt; Impairment recognition (Method II: Allocate carrying amount of shared asset / goodwill to CGUs).</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the CGU group field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Date field, enter a date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enter the date on which to post the impairment transaction.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Description field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Recognition test.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Run test.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The recognition test will compare the sum of the net book value with the undiscounted cash flow of each cash generating unit to determine if calculation of the impairment amount is needed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Calculate.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If the test result is 'Yes', then the recognition test will subtract the recoverable amount from the net book value to determine the impairment adjustment amount.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The impairment adjustment amount is distributed to each of the fixed assets for posting.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Confirm.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You only can post confirmed recognition tests.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Yes.</source>
        </trans-unit>
